@minrk what do you think?

I don't think that str should always be castable. In the case of integers, strings coming from CLI/ENV should be cast from strings, but assignment (`c.int_trait = '5'`) should still fail. Part of the goal of the from_string stuff is that it should only occur in the explicit cases where all values *must* come from strings, and not any other time.

