@lkraider, keep in mind that it would need to be a "classproperty" in order to provide class-level access.  Something like this:

```python
class classproperty(object):
    def __init__(self, func):
        self.func = func
    def __get__(self, inst, klass):
        return self.func(klass)

class MyType(BaseType):
    @classproperty
    def PRIMITIVE_TYPE(cls):
        return str if cls.whatever else int
```

