Hi @gwind, in the mutation in relay (in the client) you have to specify the output you want when you do the `signin` mutation ([example](https://github.com/graphql-python/graphene/blob/master/examples/starwars_relay/tests/test_mutation.py#L11-L25))

The `clientMutationId` output field is automatically added by relay, however you must add the data you want to get to.

Right now you seem to do something like that in the client
```graphql
mutation Signin {
    signin(input:$input_0)
}
```
when you should do:

```graphql
mutation Signin {
    signin(input:$input_0) {
        session {
             id
        }
    }
}
```

Or something like that... does that makes sense?

